--------------------------

Subject to the terms that apply to the original ZML code and to any other
third-party material in this repository, the original authors grant permission
to use, copy, modify, and run the new experimental material in this repository
for private experimentation and evaluation.

If you redistribute this repository or work derived from it, please:

1. Preserve this notice and the applicable upstream and third-party notices.
2. Clearly identify your changes and do not imply endorsement by ZML or its
   maintainers.
3. Do not present this experimental fork as an official ZML release.
4. Share useful, generally applicable improvements with ZML when doing so is
   practical. This is a request made in the spirit of collaboration, not a
   demand that every notebook, benchmark, or embarrassing prototype become a
   public artifact.
5. Keep private credentials, proprietary data, and environment-specific
   deployment details out of copies and distributions.

Nothing in this notice grants rights to ZML's name, trademarks, logos, or
other third-party works beyond the permissions already granted by their own
licenses. This repository is not an official ZML project, release, fork
maintained by ZML, or representation of ZML's views. Read the relevant
upstream and third-party license files before redistributing anything. In case
of conflict, those licenses control the material they cover.

